5000|$|Rabbi Israel Weiss {{was born}} in Czechoslovakia. He studied at Mercaz HaRav in Jerusalem. In 1976, he was drafted into the Miilitary Rabbinate and served as <b>a</b> {{battalion}} <b>rabbi,</b> <b>a</b> brigade <b>rabbi,</b> <b>a</b> division <b>rabbi,</b> and the rabbi of GOC Army Headquarters. In 2000, Weiss was nominated to the position after Rabbi Gad Navon stepped down. Weiss {{was present at the}} 2008 Israel-Hezbollah prisoner exchange and remarked of the bodies that Hezbollah released: [...] "the verification process yesterday was very slow, because, if we thought the enemy was cruel to the living and the dead, we were surprised, when we opened the caskets, to discover just how cruel. And I'll leave it at that." ...|$|R
