50|$|Meshulam Dovid Soloveitchik (known as Reb or Rav Dovid) (born 1921) (משולם דוד סולובייצ'יק) is <b>an</b> Orthodox <b>rabbi</b> and rosh yeshiva {{of one of}} the {{branches}} of the Brisk yeshivas in Jerusalem, Israel, attended by select young Talmudists, mainly from the United States. He is <b>a</b> son of <b>Rabbi</b> Yitzchak Zev Soloveitchik, <b>a</b> son-in-law of <b>Rabbi</b> Osher Sternbuch of London and <b>a</b> brother-in-law of <b>Rabbi</b> Moishe Sternbuch and Dayan Chanoch Ehrentreu.|$|R
