50|$|Auerbach was {{descended from}} an illustrious line of Hasidic leaders. His father was Rabbi Avraham Dov Auerbach, the Admor of Chernowitz-Chmielnik, Poland, who was <b>a</b> {{son-in-law}} of <b>Rabbi</b> Tzvi Halberstam, {{son of the}} Divrei Chaim of Sanz. Rabbi Avraham Dov was <b>a</b> son of <b>Rabbi</b> Yehuda Dov Auerbach of Tsfat and Jerusalem, who was <b>a</b> son of <b>Rabbi</b> Yoel Faivel Stein. who was <b>a</b> son-in-law of <b>Rabbi</b> Avraham Dov of Chmielnik, <b>a</b> son-in-law of <b>Rabbi</b> Jacob Joseph of Polonne, the Baal Shem Tov's most prominent disciple and author of Toldos Yaakov Yosef on Hasidic thought.|$|R
